OL,6,F"Information you hold could be vital
OL,7,Fto our investigation.J"Speak to our
OL,8,Fofficers directly or come forward
OL,9,Fanonymously and we will take swift
OL,10,Faction to remove dangerous weapons and
OL,11,Fthose who use them from our streets."
OL,12,FAnyone who witnessed the incident or
OL,13,Fwho has any information is asked to
OL,14,Fcontact @MerPolCC on Twitter or
OL,15,F'Merseyside Police Contact Centre' on
OL,16,FFacebook with log 640 of Monday 29
OL,17,FJanuary.
